Second Lady Karen Pence was honored with the Courage Award by Tracy's Kids Art Therapy Program for her support of art therapy programs for young cancer patients. The award recognizes the strength and perseverance of cancer patients and is given to public figures who have worked to address the challenges of the disease. Mrs. Pence has been involved with Tracy's Kids since 2011 and serves as the Honorary Chair of the Art Therapy Initiative at Riley Hospital for Children. She has also made it a priority to visit hospitals in the US and abroad to see art therapists in action. Tracy's Kids provides art therapy programs at no cost to children and families at seven clinics across the country.